print:\u003c/strong\u003e Chair Kevin Warsh is framed as taking active control of the Open Market Desk, with desks shifting away from forward guidance toward spot-market price discovery.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Death of the Shelter Lag:\u003c/strong\u003e The desk narrative remains focused on spot commodity and energy inputs as a hawkish baseline, explaining elevated term premium and MOVE pressure.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128200; Trading Strategy Note (ES Futures)\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrder Flow Layout:\u003c/strong\u003e As institutional cash volume returns post-holiday, liquidity maps on the 1.5k volume chart in MotiveWave are expected to face the cleanest volatility window around the 22:00 GMT+8 Consumer Confidence print. Focus execution on absorbed extensions at VAL/VAH rather than chasing momentum bars.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Williams Rule:\u003c/strong\u003e Seasonal cycle frameworks keep June 16 as the target profile for a sustainable primary market floor. Maintain size discipline; loose NFCI keeps the macro bull structure backstopped, while redlining bond volatility leaves room for wider technical sweeps through the rest of May.\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e"
